\begin_layout Author
Gaoli Chen
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The author would like to thank the referee for the valuable remarks regarding
 the submission DE12221.
 The remarks motivated the author to reexamine the calculation of the vertex
 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{rpq}$
\end_inset

 and corrected an error on it.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The statement that 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{rpq}$
\end_inset

 vanishes if 
\begin_inset Formula $sKL$
\end_inset

 is odd is incorrect.
 It was due to a mistake in equation (4.9), which was an unnumbered equation
 in the first submission.
 To correct the error, the author made the following changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Remove the relevant remarks about the statement from the paper: 1) The second
 sentence of the abstract.
 2) The sentence 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

These improvements lead to ...
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 in the first bullet of the Introduction.
 3) The first paragraph of the subsection 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

4.1 Remarks on Vertices
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Correct the calculation error of equation (4.9).
 Previously, the result of the calculation was 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(-\right)^{g_{p}g_{q}}\tilde{W}_{rqp}=\left(-\right)^{sKL}\tilde{W}_{rpq}$
\end_inset

, which implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{rpq}=\frac{1}{2}\left(\tilde{W}_{rpq}+\left(-\right)^{g_{p}g_{q}}\tilde{W}_{rqp}\right)=0$
\end_inset

 if 
\begin_inset Formula $sKL=0$
\end_inset

.
 In the second line of the equation, the author shifted the variables as
 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{i}\to\theta_{i+K}$
\end_inset

 in the integrand and assumed that the integral does not change.
 This is incorrect.
 The integral is only invariant under the cyclic shift among the subset
 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \theta_{1},\cdots,\theta_{L}\right\} $
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \theta_{L+1},\cdots,\theta_{M}\right\} $
\end_inset

 but not the entire set.
 After the correction, the new result is 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{W}_{rqp}=\left(-\right)^{g_{p}g_{q}}\tilde{W}_{rpq}$
\end_inset

, which implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{W}_{rqp}$
\end_inset

 is already (anti-)symmetrized over 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{rpq}=\tilde{W}_{rpq}$
\end_inset

.
 The technical details are explained in the main text after the equation
 (4.9) and the footnote 3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The author would like to stress that, in addition to the second point mentioned
 in the referee report, the paper provides a formalism to calculate the
 interaction vertices via the calculation of the vacuum expectation values
 of ladder operators.
 This is important because it is necessary for the use of interaction vertex
 in calculations of observables.
\end_layout

